Magpie Custom Creations seeks to raise the profile of sewing and handicrafts as a valid and valuable art form and promote the recycling and re-use of fiber and decorative materials. We currently represent seven independent fiber and jewelry artists and a rotating group of painters and sculptors in our small shop in Cortland, NY. I've been given the opportunity to apply for a citywide Microenterprise Grant for Magpie but I must supply 10% equity to have access to the money.  This is where you can help!  Please consider making Magpie's holiday season merry by contributing toward my goal.  Here is how Microenterprise Grant funds will help my business work smarter and faster:
-an updated and functional computer system
to streamline the shop's retail procedures (no more handwritten receipts! Hooray!);
-advertising funds to assist in spreading
the word about Magpie’s offerings outside the immediate city of Cortland;
-a dedicated website to drive online
sales and outreach (so many of you have asked for this!);
-additional machinery and supplies
(i.e. sewing machines, sergers, tables, scissors, thread, fabric, manuals,
etc.) so we can start holding classes;
-funds to hire a part-time
administrative assistant/bookkeeper to assist with business operations; thus freeing up the seamstress to create more work;
-ability to hire several part-time
assistants to help on the shop floor and teach classes.Though business is quite robust,  I'm still just covering day to day expenses. Right now, all business operations and custom services, repairs, and alterations at Magpie are performed by me. Please help me share the wealth with other talented individuals, and give Magpie a chance to continue growing, thriving, and expanding!
